---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/ui/PageHero.astro';
import GuideShell from '../../components/guides/GuideShell.astro';
import ChatMock from '../../components/guides/ChatMock.astro';
import DashFrame from '../../components/guides/DashFrame.astro';

const sections = [
    { id: 'connect', heading: 'Connect your channel', note: 'One Twitch sign-in. No API keys, no config files, nothing to install.' },
    { id: 'tour', heading: 'Find your way around', note: 'Five stops in the floating dock. You will spend most of your time in two of them.' },
    { id: 'first-command', heading: 'Create your first command', note: 'A name and a response. Everything else is optional.' },
    { id: 'first-module', heading: 'Switch on your first module', note: 'Modules are bigger features with an on/off switch. Two are already on for you.' },
    { id: 'go-live', heading: 'Go live with confidence', note: 'A two-minute pre-stream checklist, then the bot takes the night shift.' },
];
---

<Layout
    title="Getting started — ItsBagelBot Guides"
    description="Set up ItsBagelBot in minutes: connect your Twitch channel, tour the dashboard, create your first command, and switch on your first module."
    ogType="article"
>
    <PageHero
        eyebrow="Guide 01"
        title="Getting started"
        description="From “Add to Twitch” to your first stream with the bot in chat. Ten minutes, start to finish, most of it reading."
    />

    <GuideShell
        sections={sections}
        minutes="6 min read"
        next={{ href: '/guides/commands', label: 'Commands & variables' }}
    >
        <Fragment slot="connect">
            <p>
                Head to <a href="https://dashboard.itsbagelbot.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">dashboard.itsbagelbot.com</a>
                and sign in with your Twitch account. Twitch shows you exactly what the bot is allowed
                to do before you approve anything, and that's the whole setup. The moment you're in,
                ItsBagelBot joins your chat and sits quietly until it's spoken to.
            </p>
            <ChatMock
                title="#your_channel"
                caption="What your chat sees, about two seconds after you sign in."
                lines={[
                    { who: 'system', text: 'itsbagelbot joined #your_channel' },
                    { who: 'viewer', name: 'maya_live', text: 'oh a new bot, hi!' },
                ]}
            />
            <p class="gtip">
                <b>Good to know</b>
                The bot never speaks unprompted. Until you create commands or enable modules, joining
                is the only thing it does: your chat stays exactly as it was.
            </p>
        </Fragment>

        <Fragment slot="tour">
            <p>
                The dashboard is one page at a time, and its whole navigation is the floating dock
                at the bottom of the screen, the same on desktop and phone. <strong>Overview</strong>
                is your landing page, <strong>Commands</strong> is where custom chat commands live, and
                <strong>Modules</strong> holds every bigger feature. Billing and Settings do what they
                say on the tin.
            </p>
            <DashFrame
                path="/"
                caption="The Overview page. Navigation lives in the floating dock at the bottom."
                notes={[
                    { n: 1, text: 'The dock is the whole navigation, on every screen size: Overview, Commands, Modules, Billing, Settings.' },
                    { n: 2, text: 'Bot status: whether ItsBagelBot is sitting in your chat right now, and the one button to fix it if not.' },
                    { n: 3, text: 'Quick actions: the two things you will do most, one tap away.' },
                    { n: 4, text: 'Your most-used commands live here too, one click from editing.' },
                ]}
            >
                <div class="df-main">
                    <div class="df-topbar"><span class="df-brand">ItsBagelBot <small>Console</small></span><span class="df-crumb">ItsBagelBot / <b>Overview</b></span><span class="df-account">streamer · Broadcaster</span></div>
                    <span class="df-eyebrow">Status</span>
                    <p class="df-title">Good evening, <i>streamer</i></p>
                    <div class="df-row"><span class="df-grow"><b style="color:var(--white);">Online · in chat</b> · nothing needs you right now</span><span class="df-btn df-btn--ghost">Restart</span><span class="df-btn df-btn--ghost">Disconnect</span><i class="df-dot" style="position:static;">2</i></div>
                    <span class="df-cat">Quick actions</span>
                    <div class="df-actions"><span class="df-btn df-btn--primary">+ New command</span><span class="df-btn df-btn--ghost">Manage modules</span><i class="df-dot" style="position:static;">3</i></div>
                    <span class="df-cat">Your top commands <i class="df-dot" style="position:static; width:16px; height:16px; font-size:0.55rem; margin-left:4px;">4</i></span>
                    <div class="df-row"><code>!bagel</code><span class="df-grow">&#123;user&#125; tosses a warm bagel to &#123;target&#125;. Toasty.</span><span class="df-meta"><b>1.2k</b> uses</span></div>
                    <div class="df-row"><code>!lurk</code><span class="df-grow">&#123;user&#125; fades into the shadows. Thanks for the lurk.</span><span class="df-meta"><b>521</b> uses</span></div>
                    <div class="df-dock"><span class="is-active">Overview</span><span>Commands</span><span>Modules</span><span>Billing</span><span>Settings</span><i class="df-dot" style="position:static; align-self:center; margin-left:6px;">1</i></div>
                </div>
            </DashFrame>
            <p>
                Everything on the dashboard saves the moment you confirm it: there's no "deploy" step,
                and changes reach your chat within seconds.
            </p>
        </Fragment>

        <Fragment slot="first-command">
            <p>
                Open <strong>Commands</strong> and press <strong>New command</strong>. A command needs
                exactly two things: a <strong>name</strong> (what viewers type after the
                <code>!</code>) and a <strong>response</strong> (what the bot says back). Let's make
                the classic:
            </p>
            <DashFrame
                path="/commands"
                caption="The Commands page: your list on the left, the editor docked on the right."
                notes={[
                    { n: 1, text: 'New command opens the editor, docked beside the list on desktop (a bottom sheet on phones).' },
                    { n: 2, text: 'The name, without the “!” (the dashboard adds it in chat). Lowercase, no spaces.' },
                    { n: 3, text: 'The response. Plain text is fine; the next guide shows the variables that make it smart.' },
                    { n: 4, text: 'Create saves it instantly. The command works in chat from this moment.' },
                ]}
            >
                <div class="df-main">
                    <div class="df-topbar"><span class="df-brand">ItsBagelBot <small>Console</small></span><span class="df-crumb">ItsBagelBot / <b>Commands</b></span><span class="df-account">streamer · Broadcaster</span></div>
                    <span class="df-eyebrow">Manage</span>
                    <p class="df-title">Chat <i>commands</i></p>
                    <div class="df-toolbar">
                        <span class="df-pill df-pill--tan">All</span>
                        <span class="df-pill df-pill--off">Active</span>
                        <span class="df-pill df-pill--off">Custom</span>
                        <span class="df-spacer"></span>
                        <span class="df-search">Search name, alias, response…</span>
                        <span class="df-btn df-btn--tan">+ New command</span>
                        <i class="df-dot" style="position:static;">1</i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="df-cols">
                        <div style="display:grid; gap:8px; align-content:start;">
                            <div class="df-row"><span class="df-num">01</span><code>!followage</code><span class="df-pill df-pill--on">built-in</span><span class="df-grow"></span><span class="df-meta">Everyone · 15s</span><span class="df-toggle is-on"></span></div>
                            <div class="df-row is-open"><span class="df-num">02</span><code>!discord</code><span class="df-grow">Come hang out between streams…</span><span class="df-meta">Everyone · 0s</span><span class="df-toggle is-on"></span></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="df-panel">
                            <div class="df-panel-head">New command <i>✕</i></div>
                            <div class="df-field"><span>Name</span><div class="df-input is-focus">discord<i class="df-dot" style="position:static; margin-left:auto;">2</i></div></div>
                            <div class="df-field"><span>Response</span><div class="df-input">Come hang out between streams → discord.gg/your-invite<i class="df-dot" style="position:static; margin-left:auto;">3</i></div></div>
                            <div class="df-chat">
                                <span class="df-chat-tag">Chat rehearsal</span>
                                <p class="df-viewer"><b>sesame_sam</b><span>!discord</span></p>
                                <p class="df-bot"><b>ItsBagelBot</b><span>Come hang out between streams → discord.gg/your-invite</span></p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="df-panel-foot"><span class="df-btn df-btn--ghost">Cancel</span><span class="df-btn df-btn--tan">✓ Create</span><i class="df-dot" style="position:static;">4</i></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="df-dock"><span>Overview</span><span class="is-active">Commands</span><span>Modules</span><span>Billing</span><span>Settings</span></div>
                </div>
            </DashFrame>
            <ChatMock
                title="#your_channel"
                caption="Thirty seconds later, in chat."
                lines={[
                    { who: 'viewer', name: 'maya_live', text: '!discord' },
                    { who: 'bot', text: 'Come hang out between streams → discord.gg/your-invite' },
                ]}
            />
            <p>
                The editor also offers access levels (everyone → broadcaster), a cooldown, and a
                "only while live" switch, all optional, all explained in the
                <a href="/guides/commands">commands guide</a>.
            </p>
        </Fragment>

        <Fragment slot="first-module">
            <p>
                Head to <strong>Modules</strong>. Each tile is one feature with its own switch, and
                clicking a tile opens its settings. Two are already working for you out of the box:
                <strong>Chat Alerts</strong> (follows, subs, cheers, raids) and <strong>AutoMod</strong>
                (the layered moderation you read about on the homepage).
            </p>
            <DashFrame
                path="/modules"
                caption="The Modules page: a category rail on the left, tiles with a Configure button and a switch."
                notes={[
                    { n: 1, text: 'Already on: alerts thank followers and subs with a message you can rewrite.' },
                    { n: 2, text: "Opt-in: timers post a message on a schedule while you're live. Great for the Discord plug." },
                ]}
            >
                <div class="df-main">
                    <div class="df-topbar"><span class="df-brand">ItsBagelBot <small>Console</small></span><span class="df-crumb">ItsBagelBot / <b>Modules</b></span><span class="df-account">streamer · Broadcaster</span></div>
                    <span class="df-eyebrow">Manage</span>
                    <p class="df-title">Channel <i>modules</i></p>
                    <p class="df-sub">Optional features for your channel. 1 of 13 enabled.</p>
                    <div class="df-search" style="max-width:200px;">Search modules…</div>
                    <div class="df-cols df-cols--rail">
                        <div class="df-rail"><b>Categories</b><span class="is-active">Chat Tools</span><span>Community</span><span>Games</span></div>
                        <div style="display:grid; gap:10px; align-content:start;">
                            <span class="df-cat">Chat Tools</span>
                            <div class="df-grid">
                                <div class="df-tile"><div class="df-tile-head"><i class="df-ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><polyline points="12 7 12 12 15 14"/></svg></i><span><b>Timers</b><small>Chat Tools</small></span></div><small>Post repeating chat messages on a schedule while you are live.</small><div class="df-tile-foot"><span class="df-btn--configure">Configure</span><span class="df-toggle"></span></div><i class="df-dot" style="top:10px; right:10px;">2</i></div>
                                <div class="df-tile"><div class="df-tile-head"><i class="df-ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 7V5a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h14a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v2"/><path d="M9 20h6"/><path d="M12 4v16"/></svg></i><span><b>Trigger Words</b><small>Chat Tools</small></span></div><small>Auto-reply when a word shows up in chat.</small><div class="df-tile-foot"><span class="df-btn--configure">Configure</span><span class="df-toggle"></span></div></div>
                            </div>
                            <span class="df-cat">Community</span>
                            <div class="df-grid">
                                <div class="df-tile"><div class="df-tile-head"><i class="df-ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M18 8a6 6 0 0 0-12 0c0 7-3 9-3 9h18s-3-2-3-9"/><path d="M13.7 21a2 2 0 0 1-3.4 0"/></svg></i><span><b>Chat Alerts</b><small>Community</small></span></div><small>Announce follows, subs, cheers and raids in chat.</small><div class="df-tile-foot"><span class="df-btn--configure">Configure</span><span class="df-toggle is-on"></span></div><i class="df-dot" style="top:10px; right:10px;">1</i></div>
                                <div class="df-tile"><div class="df-tile-head"><i class="df-ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 11l19-9-9 19-2-8-8-2z"/></svg></i><span><b>Auto Shoutout</b><small>Community</small></span></div><small>Welcome incoming raids with an automatic shoutout.</small><div class="df-tile-foot"><span class="df-btn--configure">Configure</span><span class="df-toggle"></span></div></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="df-dock"><span>Overview</span><span>Commands</span><span class="is-active">Modules</span><span>Billing</span><span>Settings</span></div>
                </div>
            </DashFrame>
            <p>
                Nothing here is dangerous to poke: every module can be switched off as quickly as it
                came on, and its settings are kept for the next time. The full tour of what each one
                does lives in the <a href="/guides/modules">modules handbook</a>.
            </p>
        </Fragment>

        <Fragment slot="go-live">
            <p>Before your next stream, a quick rehearsal:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Type your new command in chat yourself: the bot answers you like any viewer.</li>
                <li>Skim the <strong>Chat Alerts</strong> messages and make them sound like you.</li>
                <li>Raided often? Switch on <strong>Auto Shoutout</strong> so incoming raiders get greeted even when you're mid-game.</li>
            </ol>
            <p>
                That's the whole setup. The bot moderates, greets, and answers on its own from here,
                and everything you just did can be changed mid-stream from your phone.
            </p>
            <p class="gtip">
                <b>Next up</b>
                Make your commands smart: <a href="/guides/commands">Commands &amp; variables</a> shows
                how one line like <code>Welcome, &lbrace;user&rbrace;!</code> greets every viewer by name.
            </p>
        </Fragment>
    </GuideShell>
</Layout>
